    "summary": "I'm an Environmental Health and Safety Professional with 13+ years of senior management experience and 22+ years of combined industry experience. During this period, I\u2019ve successfully managed the legislative and regulatory aspects of compliance and the human aspects (i.e. workplace behaviour), at a bio-refinery complex. I have two broad areas of HSE management responsibility, although they overlap considerably: Health & Safety, and Environmental. \n\nMy role is to provide leadership and expertise on all issues connected to health, safety and the environment, to enforce risk management compliance company-wide and across all our bio-refinery sites, and to continuously review and upgrade our emergency response plans. I lead all risk- and safety-related studies, analysis, planning, hazard identification, mitigation preparedness and response implementation, and contribute to collaborative internal and external HSE audits. I also record and manage investigations, and make recommendations for corrective \u2013 and, better still -- preventative actions: Anticipation and prevention is the core of top effective HSE Compliance.\n\nForeseeing the health, safety and environmental impact of human actions in the workplace is as important as understanding and implementing the actual HSE legislation and regulation. Much of my work, therefore, involves promoting HSE compliance by ensuring employees carry out their individual and team responsibilities diligently. Here, my interpersonal communications skills are indispensable: the ability to motivate and mentor individuals, to build and lead teams, to run effective training sessions and workshops, and to negotiate. HSE Compliance works best when the entire team is on board and fully cognizant of their roles and responsibilities and procedures to follow.",
